      • getVaccinesNeeded

        public static int getVaccinesNeeded(Data data,
                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> distributionCentre,
                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer>> availabilities,
                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> bookablePeople,
                                    java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> vans,
                                    int totalVaccinesPerHour,
                                    int totalCapacity,
                                    double totalDistance,
                                    int totalVaccinesNeeded)
        Gets the number of vaccines the given distribution centre needs to fulfill the needs of the nearby vaccination centres for the next week, based off the predicted needs of nearby vaccination centres and how much of their needs need to be met by the given dsitribution centre
        Parameters:
        data -
        distributionCentre - the distribution centre that needs more vaccines
        availabilities - how many people have already booked vaccines, in the format HashMap>
        bookablePeople - everyone eligible to be booked, in the format HashMap>
        totalVaccinesPerHour - the number of vaccinations all vaccination centres can perform each hour
        totalCapacity - the storage capacity of all vaccination centres
        totalDistance - distance between all vaccination centres and all distribution centres. Used to help determine the proportion of total vaccination centre demand each distribution centre should be fulfilling
        totalVaccinesNeeded - the number of vaccines needed to be ordered for all vaccination centres to fulfill all current and predicted bookings for the next week. Used to help determine the demand from each vaccination centre.
        Returns:
        the number of vaccines the given distribution centre needs
